Assessing Data¶

In this section, detect and document at least eight (8) quality issues and two (2) tidiness issue. You must use both visual assessment programmatic assessement to assess the data.

Note: pay attention to the following key points when you access the data.

  • You only want original ratings (no retweets) that have images. Though there are 5000+ tweets in the dataset, not all are dog ratings and some are retweets.
  • Assessing and cleaning the entire dataset completely would require a lot of time, and is not necessary to practice and demonstrate your skills in data wrangling. Therefore, the requirements of this project are only to assess and clean at least 8 quality issues and at least 2 tidiness issues in this dataset.
  • The fact that the rating numerators are greater than the denominators does not need to be cleaned. This unique rating system is a big part of the popularity of WeRateDogs.
  • You do not need to gather the tweets beyond August 1st, 2017. You can, but note that you won't be able to gather the image predictions for these tweets since you don't have access to the algorithm used.

Quality issues¶

  1. There are retweets present in tweets_arch columns

  2. Retweets in rows (rows that start with 'RT @')

  3. Timestamp format is object(string) and tweet_id format is int

  4. Invalid dog names in tweets_arch

  5. Tweet source can be extracted in tweets_arch

  6. Inconsistency in p1,p2,p3 string cases in images

  7. Outliers in rating_denominator in tweets_arch

  8. Outliers in rating_numerator in tweets_arch

  9. Some of the values in images are not dogs

  10. Some columns are unnecessary for analysis

  11. Non descriptive column names

Tidiness issues¶

  1. The three datasets should be merged as they are part of the same observational unit(tweets)
  2. dogstages is spread across four columns instead of one column in tweets_arch

Issue #2:¶

Define¶

  • Write a function that converts dog stages into a single column rather than having the dog stage values as columns, then drop the doggo, floofer, pupper and puppo columns

  • This function creates a new column 'dog_stage' and fills it with the value from the either the doggo, floofer, pupper or puppo column, where it is not 'None'.

  • If all the values in the rows of the columns are 'None', it replaces with NA.
  • If there is more than one null value, it concatenates the values

Code¶

In [26]:
def dogstage(df, columns):
    for column in columns:
        df[column] = df[column].replace('None',np.NaN)
    df["dogstage"] = df[columns].apply(lambda x: ','.join(x.dropna()), axis=1)
    df["dogstage"] = df["dogstage"].replace('', 'NA')
    return df
columns = ['doggo','floofer','pupper','puppo']
df = dogstage(df, columns)
In [27]:
#drop the former columns
df = df.drop(['doggo','floofer','pupper','puppo'], axis = 1)

Code¶

In [41]:
def titlecase(df, columns):
    for col in columns:
        df[col] = df[col].str.title()
    return df
